Overview

The system follows a simple web-based architecture consisting of a frontend interface, backend services, and a database.
The system follows a simple web-based architecture consisting of a frontend interface, backend services, and a database. It also integrates with email services for sending reminders.

System Context Diagram (level 1)

This diagram shows how the system interacts with external users and services.

C4Context
title System Context Diagram

Person(student, "Student", "Uses the system to manage assignments")
System(system, "Assignment Tracker System", "Tracks assignments and sends reminders")
System_Ext(email, "Email Service", "Sends notifications")

Rel(student, system, "Uses")
Rel(system, email, "Sends reminders via")

So the student is the primary user of the system.
The system processes assignment data and sends reminders.
An external email service is used for notifications. 


Container Diagram (level 2)

This diagram shows the high level technical structure of the system.

C4Container
title Container Diagram 

Person(student, "Student")

Container(webapp, "Web Application", "HTML/CSS/JS", "User interface for students")
Container(api, "Backend API", "Node.js / Flask", "Handles business logic")
Container(db, "Database", "MySQL / MongoDB", "Stores assignment data")

System_Ext(email, "Email Service")

Rel(student, webapp, "Uses")
Rel(webapp, api, "API Calls")
Rel(api, db, "Reads/Writes")
Rel(api, email, "Sends reminders")

So here the Web Application allows user interaction.
The Backend API processes logic and handles requests.
The Database stores all assignment data.
The Email Service sends reminders to users.


Component Diagram  level 3

This diagram shows internal backend components.

C4Component
title Component Diagram 

Container(api, "Backend API")

Component(auth, "Authentication Module", "Handles login/signup")
Component(assign, "Assignment Module", "Manages assignments")
Component(reminder, "Reminder Module", "Schedules notifications")

Rel(auth, assign, "Access control")
Rel(assign, reminder, "Triggers reminders")

So here the Authentication Module manages user access.
The Assignment Module handles assignment operations.
The Reminder Module manages scheduling and notifications

End-to-End System Flow

The student logs into the system
The student adds an assignment
The system stores the assignment in the database
The reminder module schedules a notification
The system sends a reminder via email before the deadline

This flow demonstrates how the system components interact to deliver the required functionality.


